<div><h3>IMED 3010 - Graduate Studio </h3>  <p><hr>This course is to be taken by BSDT MFA students to work alongside undergraduate students in the BSDT Game Studio course structure. MFA students take on the role of Team Lead/Producer for this course and manage a team of undergraduate students to complete an interactive media project; which may include serious games, simulations, artistic installations, entertainment, or new technological exploration. The course will provide a hands-on development environment for a formal interactive title to be released. Students will gain experience working as a Team Lead of a game studio team with various departments, skill-levels, development infrastructures, and real-world demands. Students are required to take this course twice, the first and second semesters of their MFA degree.</p>

<p><em>Repeatable for credit.</em><br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Fall and Spring<br><br></p></div>		</td>
